        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 8:32PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 832 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Middlefield, or 12 miles southeast of Chardon, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Middlefield, Burton, Huntsburg, Claridon, Montville, and Aquilla.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
